This topic describes how to resolve common issues with **Altoros Log Search of Pivotal Platform**.

##<a id='cluster-health'></a> Verify Log Search Cluster Health

Follow these steps to verify **Altoros Log Search for Pivotal Platform** cluster health:

1. In the **Altoros Log Search for Pivotal Platform** tile, click **Status** and record the IP address of the Elasticsearch Master instance.
1. SSH into Pivotal Platform Ops Manager instance.
1. Execute the next command to check the current Elasticsearch cluster state:
    ```
    curl ELASTICSEARCH-MASTER-INSTANCE-IP:9200/_cluster/health
    ```

